1
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:53,200
We’re starting to act more and more like a married couple?

2
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:55,080
Don't be shy, wifey!

3
00:00:56,560 --> 00:00:58,440
The very first First Class flight...

4
00:00:58,440 --> 00:01:00,160
is about to begin.

5
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:02,360
These are the passengers for your very first flight.

6
00:01:02,760 --> 00:01:04,480
New Money and Old Money.

7
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:08,760
Is this really a First Class airline?

8
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:12,240
I am so sorry

9
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:14,960
for hitting Ms. Cow Cow, right in the face.

10
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:16,560
It's Crown, not Cow.

11
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:20,960
There is definitely a flight attendant on this flight
who will not be moving forward with us.

12
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:29,800
Are you nervous?

13
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:30,480
Very.

14
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,680
So very much.

15
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:34,560
If I were you, I’d be nervous too.

16
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:38,040
The very first First Class flight...

17
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:39,760
is about to begin.

18
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:41,160
No.

19
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:43,560
No what?

20
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:45,960
I'm not ready yet.

21
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:48,080
Can I have a little more time, please?

22
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:49,680
Dr. Yep said...

23
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:53,000
my facial structure is gorgeous, like Davika.

24
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:56,360
Huh? Davika Howling, you mean!

25
00:01:56,360 --> 00:01:59,720
If passengers see this, they’ll howl in shock. Even kids will cry!

26
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:01,120
It’s too late now.

27
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:04,120
Because I have already confirmed the appointments with both passengers.

28
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:12,440
This lady is Ms. Mongkut Karattri Wijitsakul.

29
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:16,440
Or as high society calls her...Ms. Crown.

30
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:20,360
A young lady of undeniable beauty, both in face and personality.

31
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:23,800
Ms. Crown treats people of all levels with respect,
she does not discriminate.

32
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:27,920
When it comes to dressing,
she prioritizes the quality of the tailoring and craftsmanship

33
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:31,000
over simply drenching herself in brand names.

34
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:34,120
The duty of the Cabin Crew in caring for Ms. Crown is

35
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:38,120
to uphold her honor and dignity at all times.

36
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:49,640
Ms. Daryl, Ms. Maximal Girl.

37
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:51,640
With a name like hers, there is no such thing as "minimal."

38
00:02:55,560 --> 00:03:00,080
Recently, Ms. Daryl went viral for her heroic act
of slapping a robber unconscious with her Hermes bag.

39
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:04,080
A lesson for any thief daring enough to try and steal her valuables.

40
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:18,360
Ms. Daryl loves anything with a groove and a beat.
She needs to stay entertained at all times.

41
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:22,360
She loves creating contents 24 hours a day.

42
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:25,800
Her only weakness is sitting still.
If the atmosphere gets dull or boring,

43
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,800
she gets stressed and frustrated.

44
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:32,240
Therefore, anyone assigned to look after Ms. Daryl on this flight

45
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:34,200
must have their energy levels fully charged.

46
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:37,200
Because she demands excitement and stimulation throughout the entire flight.

47
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:43,960
Ladies and gentlemen, these are the passengers for your very first flight.

48
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:46,160
New Money and Old Money.

49
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:47,760
New Money?

50
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:49,360
Old Money?

51
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:50,280
What does that even mean?

52
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:52,600
Ugh, it means "old wealth" and "new wealth," you idiot!

53
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:53,600
How can you not know that?

54
00:03:59,720 --> 00:04:02,000
Wait, is the passenger having a cramp or something?

55
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,200
She isn't moving at all.

56
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:05,240
Or is she...not human?

57
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:07,400
Correct.

58
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:08,320
She is not human.

59
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:12,080
Because these are wax models representing your passengers.

60
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:14,000
What???

61
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,400
This task is over-the-top!

62
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,240
They actually invested in sculpting wax figures?

63
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,920
So, how should we prepare ourselves?

64
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:21,280
I thought you’d never ask.

65
00:04:21,280 --> 00:04:23,000
I’m going to split you into two teams...

66
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,880
Team Old Money and Team New Money.

67
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:28,680
Team New Money will consist of Mr. All-New and Ms. Chaba.

68
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:32,680
As for Team Old Money, it will be Ms. Sky, Mr. Kreetha, and Ms. Tid-Gift.

69
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:37,760
But how can we tell who is New Money and who is Old Money?

70
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:39,960
Just take a look.

71
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:43,960
This one is definitely "Old." No matter how you look at it, she’s "Old."

72
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,120
I thought you said it was a wax model!

73
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,760
It’s a high-tech wax model.

74
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:51,760
It has a detection system, sensors for anyone
who dares to be disrespectful to the passengers.

75
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,400
You’ve been asking for it quite a few times now.

76
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:01,000
Old Money...New Money...

77
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,280
New Money...

78
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:04,560
See, Old Money has this sort of understated...

79
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:05,400
elegance.

80
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:08,080
New Money is more about showing off wealth

81
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:10,720
and you know, having brandnames and items...such...

82
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:12,240
I think...

83
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:13,600
You’re very smart.

84
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,000
But that’s not all of it.

85
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,760
24 hours. Everyone has 24 hours...

86
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:20,440
before the real passengers arrive.

87
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:21,440
Get ready.

88
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:27,560
All-New!

89
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:28,920
Come on, let’s help carry this.

90
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:29,920
24 hours...

91
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:32,920
Oh, I don't think the two of us will make it.

92
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:33,800
I’ll do it. Let's go.

93
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:34,560
Okay.

94
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:35,560
Let's go.

95
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:38,680
Chaba, are you okay?

96
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:41,200
Just wait until I meet the real you.

97
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:43,120
All-New, you just carry it yourself. Go!

98
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:45,440
This "wax" thing has crossed the line way too many times.

99
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:47,560
Oh! Look, now she's jumping.

100
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:51,120
You, New Money...wait until I see you.

101
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:53,000
It's okay, I'll carry her myself. Come here.

102
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:56,760
Ugh, just taking a photo should be enough.
Why are you playing along with them?

103
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:59,680
I’ll take a video of thisl

104
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:02,640
So beautiful.

105
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:03,640
Wow.

106
00:06:07,080 --> 00:06:07,920
This is so cute.

107
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,920
I want to buy one to keep at home!

108
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:21,280
Today I promise, if we sell a hundred bottles of Sleepy Bear Gummies,

109
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:24,600
I’ll definitely do a shirtless dance and show off my six-pack!

110
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:26,800
Sleepy Bear Gummies, oh Sleepy Bear Gummies, make you sleep deep.

111
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:27,680
Sleepy Bear Gummies!

112
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:29,120
Sleepy Bear Gummies, make you sleep deep.

113
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:31,640
Sleepy Bear Gummies!

114
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:33,720
Hey, why don't you take a break?

115
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:36,400
You’ve got a herniated disc and can't even fly.

116
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,880
You’re going to lose your job.

117
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:42,200
It’s because I’m at risk of losing my job that I have to sell these great products.

118
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:46,200
Diversify the risk and increase the happiness for all my customers!

119
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:50,880
Pee Mak Kha is asking if these gummies really help you sleep deep.

120
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:54,720
Very stressed lately and can't really sleep.

121
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,240
I totally understand that.

122
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:58,920
I understand that people these days

123
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:01,160
work so hard, and the stress just builds up.

124
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:03,240
You carry all that burden back home and can’t sleep, right?

125
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:06,440
And when you don't sleep, your health just goes downhill.

126
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:09,640
But if you want to sleep, here it is, Sleepy Bear Gummies.

127
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:12,360
Then I'll take three bottles!

128
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:19,080
Thank you so much!

129
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:22,200
Nowadays, husbands and wives help each other sell things on live sessions.

130
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:23,520
No!

131
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:25,480
We aren't husband and wife.

132
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:29,480
But if we were fighting over the same husband, then maybe.

133
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:36,640
Don't be shy, wifey!

134
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:38,040
I'm going to end the live session now, guys.

135
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:42,040
I've been working so hard lately that I forgot to do my "homework" with the wife.

136
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,480
Ouch! My back!

137
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:46,960
What was that just now?

138
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:48,880
I’ve got goosebumps all over.

139
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:50,720
It’s "content," okay?

140
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:51,920
People will love it!

141
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:54,040
A husband and wife working together to make a living.

142
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:57,680
It’s good, we'll get more customers. Isn't that great?

143
00:07:57,680 --> 00:08:00,400
What is wrong with you? I'm going to bed.

144
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,880
I have to wake up soon anyway.

145
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:04,440
Tomorrow, I have my first First Class flight.

146
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:05,960
It’s going to be a tough battle.

147
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:08,440
I have to deal with Old Money or whatever.

148
00:08:08,440 --> 00:08:10,840
If you were there too, it would be much better.

149
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:13,560
I want to go too, but look at my condition.

150
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:16,120
Our career is so...

151
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,360
...so uncertain, isn't it?

152
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:20,640
Even being alone, I'm already this paranoid.

153
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:23,320
If I had a kid...

154
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:26,320
I don't get it. Why do people even want to have children?

155
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:33,120
But I want one.

156
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:45,120
I think having a kid would make me a cooler, better person.

157
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:03,800
Chai, I can actually see you being a father.

158
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:10,480
Mr. All-New?

159
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:20,120
Oh, he's completely freezing.

160
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:23,440
Mr. All-New?

161
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:25,800
Were you speaking to me just now?

162
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:27,680
Yes, I was speaking to you.

163
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:30,240
You are a First Class flight attendant.

164
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:32,480
You should open up your senses

165
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:34,440
and observe the things around you.

166
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:37,040
Yes.

167
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:40,040
Or maybe I just don't have the qualifications to be anything in this world at all.

168
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:45,800
Oh, I can see that you...

169
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,000
You look lost.

170
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:50,360
I have noticed you are like a lion without a pack leader.

171
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:53,360
Yes, exactly! You can tell?

172
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:55,400
Or maybe you can be my new leader?

173
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:58,280
Leader!

174
00:09:58,280 --> 00:10:01,200
Are you crazy? How could I be your leader?

175
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:05,120
The only leader is Arsenal!

176
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:08,400
Wait, you watch soccer too? I’m a Red Devil.
Who do you support?

177
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:11,760
I am a Gooner, an Arsenal disciple.

178
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:15,760
See? You look lively again.

179
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:19,400
Thank you for talking to me.

180
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:23,400
Lately, I’ve felt like I’m all alone in this world.

181
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,760
Try to open your heart.

182
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:29,760
Let Glamorous Airline be like your home.

183
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,560
I’ll try.

184
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:36,000
By the way, which era of Arsenal do you support?

185
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,840
Since the Arsène Wenger era.

186
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,840
The legendary "Invincibles" era.

187
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:56,400
Thank you, Nurse. Thank you.

188
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:00,400
Chaba, how are you feeling?

189
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,480
My head is spinning, man.

190
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:05,360
The doctor said I’ve been exercising too hard

191
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:07,320
and not getting enough rest.

192
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:10,600
Do you think I’ll be able to handle that New Money passenger tomorrow?

193
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,360
Even that wax model...

194
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:15,080
managed to slap me into a total mess.

195
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,200
Your face is a mess?

196
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,240
Yeah!

197
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:19,040
Look at my face.

198
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:22,120
It’s a bigger mess than yours!

199
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:26,120
Dr. Yep said the wound is definitely going to scab over.

200
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,280
It won't heal in time.

201
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:32,440
And then he told me I can still live my life

202
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:34,320
just wear a mask.

203
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:37,400
Well, that’s not so bad. It’s just a surgical mask.

204
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:39,320
We’ve all lived through that before.

205
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:41,000
Surgical mask, my ass!

206
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:44,680
Wait, then what kind of mask is it?

207
00:11:44,680 --> 00:11:46,680
He called it a "Python" mask.

208
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:51,840
You mean "Phantom," right?

209
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:52,280
Fan-what?

210
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:53,800
Phantom.

211
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,200
Yeah, whatever!

212
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:58,520
How am I supposed to go to work like this?

213
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:00,160
But it actually suits you.

214
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:02,160
Suits me? You idiot!

215
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:20,360
Hello, Ms. Crown.

216
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:33,080
Welcome to Glamorous Airline.

217
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:35,200
So beautiful, so beautiful!

218
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:36,800
Bravo! Bravo! That was truly beautiful.

219
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:38,680
Thank you so much.

220
00:12:38,680 --> 00:12:40,400
I’m really impressed.

221
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:43,240
Glamorous Airline is deeply honored

222
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:46,320
to be looking after Ms. Crown on this flight.

223
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:48,200
The honor is mine.

224
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:50,520
Oh, you have such a lovely voice.

225
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,600
I take it you’re a Broadway fan?

226
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:55,800
Is that why you’re wearing the Phantom mask?

227
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:58,200
Ms. Crown, you have such a keen eye!

228
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:58,520
Yes.

229
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:00,440
I absolutely love it.

230
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:03,560
You know, Phantom of the Coachella...

231
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:06,560
Coachella? The music festival?

232
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:10,560
Sky means "Phantom of the Opera."

233
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:13,680
Sky is just a little tongue-tied today.

234
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:14,800
That's right.

235
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:16,440
That’s quite alright.

236
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:18,320
I love it too.

237
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:19,840
I’ve seen it many times.

238
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:21,240
I just love the classics.

239
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:23,000
I’m a fan of the opera style myself.

240
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:25,000
Singing in harmony without any instruments.

241
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:37,400
Wait, isn't that...A cappella?

242
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:47,360
Come on!

243
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:51,360
Oh my god!

244
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:52,640
That's such a strong move!

245
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:56,120
Oh, I love this so much!

246
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:56,800
How was that?

247
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:58,000
Thank you so much!

248
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,800
This flight is going to be so much fun.

249
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:02,640
Especially with a welcoming performance like this.

250
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:04,280
Can I take a selfie with you?

251
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:06,280
Of course, Ms. Daryl.

252
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:11,480
So classy!

253
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:16,720
Hello.

254
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:19,120
Hello.

255
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:22,880
Welcome to Glamorous Airline First Class.

256
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:25,160
I, Ms. Petchgam Ploy...

257
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:26,600
Ployglamjetz.

258
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:30,000
It is an absolute honor to look after Ms. Crown and Ms. Daryl.

259
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,000
Please enjoy your flight.

260
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:53,680
Is this really a First Class airline?

261
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:56,600
Yes, it is. Our airline provides

262
00:14:56,600 --> 00:15:00,600
a welcome service tailored to the specific status of each guest.

263
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:03,600
Alright.

264
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:04,680
Please.

265
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:06,360
After you, please.

266
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:07,160
Thank you.

267
00:15:07,160 --> 00:15:09,200
Please, step inside.

268
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:09,600
Oh my god!

269
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:10,400
This way, Ms. Daryl.

270
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:11,840
This is going to be so much fun!

271
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:20,640
Please allow me to put your shoes away for you, ma'am.

272
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:21,640
Sure, thank you.

273
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:24,840
First Class beverages...

274
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:28,840
from Glamorous Airline are served.

275
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:30,440
Oh my!

276
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:49,720
Did you actually go through the effort of doing special effects makeup

277
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:53,720
to look like a character from Phantom of the Opera?

278
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:59,720
Yes, indeed. This is part of our detailed welcome service,

279
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:03,200
showing the care we provide to every First Class passenger

280
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:07,200
on Glamorous Airline.

281
00:16:09,560 --> 00:16:11,680
Excellent.

282
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:15,680
Exactly! Ms. Crown, you really have a keen eye.

283
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:20,920
I am sorry. I placed Ms. Crown's shoes in the way myself,
which caused the incident.

284
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:22,400
It's not just that.

285
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:24,160
Can't you see that both passengers

286
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:26,480
have very different lifestyles?

287
00:16:26,480 --> 00:16:29,920
What exactly is going to happen on this flight?

288
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:33,920
Right now, your score for the Old Money side is heavily in the negatives.

289
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:36,800
Oh my! Focus, everyone!

290
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:45,040
Ahhh! Did you catch that on camera?

291
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:46,000
I got it.

292
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,640
What is this?

293
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:52,640
Are you crazy? How could you
let a passenger play badminton on the plane?

294
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:55,880
What are you doing?

295
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:58,320
Oops! I am so sorry

296
00:16:58,320 --> 00:17:03,840
for hitting Ms. Cow, Cow, right in the face.

297
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:05,800
It's Crown, not Cow.

298
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:06,360
Oh.

299
00:17:06,360 --> 00:17:07,360
Here you go.

300
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:12,240
Crown. Not "Cow" as in "savory food," right?

301
00:17:12,360 --> 00:17:17,200
Because that kind of "Cow"...
there's a saying: "Eating savory but not sweet is the habit of a peasant."

302
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:19,200
A peasant. A peasant. A peasant.

303
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:26,160
Not too harsh, but it burns!

304
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:28,440
Anyway, I must apologize again

305
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:31,520
for hitting Ms. Crown in the face with the shuttlecock.

306
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:32,720
It’s alright.

307
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:35,800
It’s a good thing it didn't hit me too hard.

308
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,480
But wouldn't it be better...

309
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:41,480
if you refrained from activities that disturb other passengers?

310
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:45,880
Ms. Crown.

311
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:48,680
I most humbly beg for your pardon...me?

312
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:50,880
Don't you mean just "pardon"?

313
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:53,160
This kind of thing will never happen again.

314
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:54,640
All-New, Chaba.

315
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,240
Find something else to do.

316
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:59,280
Okay, okay, stop. No more badminton.

317
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:02,120
Um, let me introduce myself.

318
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:06,120
I'm Daryl, Ms. Crown.

319
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:09,640
Pleased to meet you, Ms. Daryl.

320
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:13,040
If it wouldn't be too much of a bother, Ms. Crown...

321
00:18:13,040 --> 00:18:16,240
could I have one selfie with you?

322
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:18,840
Ms. Crown might want to rest.

323
00:18:18,840 --> 00:18:20,400
How about taking the selfie some other time?

324
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:24,400
I'd be happy to. We can take a selfie.

325
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:28,920
Ooh, she's so cute!

326
00:18:29,120 --> 00:18:30,280
Oh my!

327
00:18:30,280 --> 00:18:33,280
Oh, playing badminton made my face look so exhausted.

328
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:36,520
But Ms. Crown, you look absolutely beautiful.

329
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:37,760
Thank you.

330
00:18:37,760 --> 00:18:41,200
You are beautiful too, Ms. Daryl.

331
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:43,200
In your own way.

332
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:50,720
In my own way...so that means I'm not actually beautiful, right?

333
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:53,720
You have a unique beauty.

334
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:56,800
Can I not be unique? Just "beautiful."

335
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:59,640
Like, beautiful without having to add "unique" at the end.

336
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:03,640
Then how about we separate and go back to the activities we are best at?

337
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:07,760
Wow. Did you hear that?

338
00:19:07,760 --> 00:19:09,160
Did everyone hear that?

339
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:12,240
That is how a classy person tells someone to "get lost."

340
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:14,040
Then what does it sound like when a non-classy person says it?

341
00:19:14,040 --> 00:19:15,960
Get out, you idiot!

342
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:18,080
Act with some manners, you peasants!

343
00:19:18,080 --> 00:19:19,680
This is a First Class flight,

344
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:21,680
not a provincial bus station!

345
00:19:21,680 --> 00:19:24,000
Is it something like that, Ms. Crown?

346
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,040
Close enough.

347
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:28,360
See? That was so spicy!

348
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:31,720
Anyway, let's just stay out of each other's way...

349
00:19:32,560 --> 00:19:33,560
Fine by me.

350
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:38,520
And what about Ms. Chaba?

351
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:42,520
Well, Chaba is so afraid of losing her job
that her intestines are literally twisting in knots.

352
00:19:46,320 --> 00:19:48,240
Did you really let passengers play badminton on an airplane?

353
00:19:48,240 --> 00:19:49,520
The passenger requested it herself, ma'am.

354
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:52,640
And if they requested to open the cabin door and jump out,

355
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:55,000
would you just allow that too?

356
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,160
I’ll be blunt.

357
00:19:56,160 --> 00:20:00,160
There is definitely a flight attendant on this flight
who will not be moving forward with us.

358
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,280
That can't be true.

359
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:01,800
It is.

360
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,600
Nooooooo!

361
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:05,000
No...

362
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,360
I want to fly First Class!

363
00:20:06,360 --> 00:20:07,920
I still want to be a flight attendant.

364
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:10,520
In that case, both of you must fight until the very end.

365
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:12,520
Make them as impressed as possible, do you hear me?

366
00:20:12,520 --> 00:20:13,520
I will fight!

367
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:16,840
Go and handle it now!

368
00:20:19,680 --> 00:20:21,960
Chaba, before you go out to fight...

369
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:23,960
Maybe flush the toilet two or three times first?

370
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:26,560
This is the ultimate embarrassment!

371
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:37,920
Chaba, Ms. Daryl can't sit still.

372
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:39,920
I think we need to do something.

373
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:43,400
Ms. Daryl, please take a deep breath.

374
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:45,320
Breathe in.

375
00:20:45,320 --> 00:20:47,320
Hold and breathe out.

376
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:54,400
Chaba, what is that sound you're making?

377
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:56,400
ASMR.

378
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:00,560
And what sound is that?

379
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:01,480
A dog.

380
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:04,000
Let's pick another sound, please!

381
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:07,960
Uh, the sound of rain.

382
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:08,760
What kind of rain is this?

383
00:21:08,760 --> 00:21:09,760
A rainstorm.

384
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:10,200
Oh.

385
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:10,680
It’s intense!

386
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:18,400
Uh, chamomilee tea...

387
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:20,440
Without syroop...

388
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:22,080
Ms. Crown.

389
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:26,080
Thank you.

390
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:29,880
It’s "Chamomile without syrup," you idiot, Kree!

391
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:32,200
You can't even speak properly, yet you keep trying.

392
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:35,400
Sky, serve the macarons, quick!

393
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:37,640
"Macaron," not "Macaroon."

394
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:41,640
In French, it’s pronounced "Ma-ga-hong."

395
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:44,240
Ma-ga-hong.

396
00:21:46,120 --> 00:21:50,120
From La durée, served for you.

397
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:55,320
Is something wrong? Do you not like macarons?

398
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:57,160
Oops.

399
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:00,160
Sky!

400
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:02,520
We're screwed.

401
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:05,400
Between the pistachio flavor...

402
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:06,640
And the rose flavor...

403
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:10,640
Ms. Sky, you've tasted both, which one do you prefer?

404
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:15,440
Oh, well, our airline requires us to taste them first.

405
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:17,880
That way we know which flavor is the absolute best...

406
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:21,800
Before serving it to Ms. Crown.

407
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:25,800
La durée’s flavors are truly exquisite.

408
00:22:26,480 --> 00:22:30,080
But for today, the chamomile tea is enough for me.

409
00:22:30,080 --> 00:22:31,480
Um, and the macarons?

410
00:22:31,480 --> 00:22:32,600
It’s alright.

411
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:33,600
Oh, okay.

412
00:22:48,120 --> 00:22:48,880
Ms. Daryl?

413
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:49,600
Ms. Daryl, what’s wrong?

414
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:50,520
I can't take it anymore!

415
00:22:50,520 --> 00:22:53,720
Want to dance? I'll dance with you.

416
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:54,520
Would that be okay?

417
00:22:54,520 --> 00:22:55,360
It's fine!

418
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:56,920
But I feel bad for Ms. Crown.

419
00:22:56,920 --> 00:22:58,400
Ms. Daryl, don't worry about it.

420
00:22:58,400 --> 00:22:59,360
We'll just dance...silently.

421
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:01,320
Good idea.

422
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:06,520
Shall we start? One, two, three...

423
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:12,120
Oh, for goodness' sake, what is with these people?
What’s with all the dancing?

424
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:14,120
Everyone, move a bit to block Ms. Crown's view.

425
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:21,520
Ms. Crown, if you don't like this, you can tell me.

426
00:23:21,520 --> 00:23:23,520
I'll go deal with them for you.

427
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:29,000
Are they dancing to "Aserejé"?

428
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:31,800
Oh my!

429
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:34,200
Ms. Crown, you actually know "Aserejé"?

430
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:37,960
Give her a round of applause!

431
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:40,320
She knows!

432
00:23:40,320 --> 00:23:41,640
But does she really know?

433
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:42,840
Let's change the song then.

434
00:23:42,840 --> 00:23:43,840
Good!

435
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:53,520
Wait, isn't that "Deng" by Girly Cherry?

436
00:23:53,520 --> 00:23:54,360
Is that right?

437
00:23:54,360 --> 00:23:56,480
Spot on, Ms. Crown!

438
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:58,280
How did you guess that?

439
00:23:58,280 --> 00:23:59,680
They aren't even dancing in sync.

440
00:23:59,680 --> 00:24:01,200
Not being in sync is

441
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:03,800
the signature of Girly Cherry!

442
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:05,200
She gets the "signature"!

443
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:06,800
She's a true fan.

444
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:08,840
Ms. Crown, you are incredible.

445
00:24:08,840 --> 00:24:10,920
At first, I thought you...

446
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:14,920
only listened to Broadway, Beethoven, or Mozart, stuff like that.

447
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:18,040
That’s just what you all assumed. You judged me.

448
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:22,040
In reality, I enjoy all kinds of music.

449
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:25,520
She's nice, but I bet it’s not every kind.

450
00:24:25,520 --> 00:24:27,240
I have a "finishing move" song.

451
00:24:27,240 --> 00:24:29,080
I think it’s a real vintage one.

452
00:24:29,080 --> 00:24:29,600
Go for it!

453
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:30,440
It’s hard to guess.

454
00:24:30,440 --> 00:24:31,440
Go ahead!

455
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:44,120
It’s "Kin Jub Kin Jib"

456
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:48,120
I dance to this song at my family's New Year party every single year!

457
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:51,080
Bravo!

458
00:24:51,080 --> 00:24:53,080
You have excellent taste, Ms. Crown.

459
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:58,720
I believe you now, you really do listen to everything.

460
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:02,520
Actually, I really love...

461
00:25:02,520 --> 00:25:04,680
chill pop songs too.

462
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:08,000
Like the song "Just For You."

463
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:13,000
"Where have you been? Why did we only just meet?"

464
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:18,640
"If I knew the world had you, I wouldn't love anyone else."

465
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:24,040
"A million people couldn't compare to you."

466
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:26,600
"I won't look at anyone else..."

467
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:29,160
"No, No, No."

468
00:25:29,160 --> 00:25:30,360
She even nailed the "No No"!

469
00:25:30,360 --> 00:25:34,360
I am someone who truly believes and has faith in true love.

470
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:36,280
Ms. Crown, you probably didn't watch the music video...

471
00:25:36,280 --> 00:25:37,720
The lead male character dies at the end.

472
00:25:37,720 --> 00:25:38,240
Oh, really?

473
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:39,800
Yes.

474
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:41,880
I was too busy just listening to the music.

475
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:46,880
Anyway, I'm so glad to be traveling with you this time, Ms. Crown.

476
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:48,640
I’m glad too.

477
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:51,240
Honestly, I’m very happy.

478
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:55,240
Because no one has ever dared to play with me like this before.

479
00:25:59,320 --> 00:26:00,320
Back to work, everyone.

480
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:04,360
Actually, there’s one more song I like.

481
00:26:04,360 --> 00:26:05,880
Fah Rak Por (DILF)

482
00:26:05,880 --> 00:26:07,800
Ms. Crown, your taste is truly top-tier!

483
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:09,800
Even for someone from such an old, established family.

484
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:11,040
Can you show me the dance?

485
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:12,040
Certainly!

486
00:26:19,840 --> 00:26:23,760
NEXT MORNING

487
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:26,920
Isn't this a happy ending already?
What else do we have to do?

488
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:27,920
Everything was perfect, wasn't it?

489
00:26:34,520 --> 00:26:38,520
Welcome to The Weakest Link.

490
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:43,560
I will call your name, and you must answer immediately.

491
00:26:43,560 --> 00:26:45,440
Mr. All-New.

492
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:47,480
Who is the person who least deserves to move forward?

493
00:26:47,480 --> 00:26:48,240
Uh...

494
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:49,720
Answer!

495
00:26:49,720 --> 00:26:51,880
Everyone...

496
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:54,280
The fact that we survived this flight, I think it was just a fluke.

497
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:56,400
Good that you realize it. Ms. Tid-Gift...

498
00:26:56,400 --> 00:26:57,280
Yes?

499
00:26:57,280 --> 00:26:59,840
What was the worst thing you did on this flight?

500
00:26:59,840 --> 00:27:02,240
Being nosy.

501
00:27:02,240 --> 00:27:06,240
When I tried to stop Ms. Crown from taking a selfie with Ms. Daryl.

502
00:27:06,440 --> 00:27:08,520
That’s correct.

503
00:27:08,520 --> 00:27:09,560
Mr. Kreetha.

504
00:27:09,560 --> 00:27:12,800
Pronounce this in English after me. Y-E-S.

505
00:27:12,800 --> 00:27:13,520
Yes.

506
00:27:13,520 --> 00:27:15,680
E-Y-E-S.

507
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:17,440
E-yes.

508
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:20,240
EYES!

509
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:20,840
Eyes, ma'am.

510
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:23,120
Please take more English lessons.

511
00:27:23,120 --> 00:27:24,240
Ms. Sky.

512
00:27:24,760 --> 00:27:26,600
Who is the weakest link in your team?

513
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:28,680
It's Chaba. She has diarrhea.

514
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:31,120
Sky! What about your macaron crumbs?

515
00:27:31,120 --> 00:27:34,560
They almost flew into the passenger's eye and blinded her!

516
00:27:34,560 --> 00:27:36,640
Team Old Money votes to kick Chaba out.

517
00:27:36,640 --> 00:27:37,840
You can’t do that.

518
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:40,640
You have no right to force anyone to vote.
Have some manners.

519
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:42,640
Yeah, just a little bit of manners.

520
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:46,040
It is time to vote.

521
00:27:46,040 --> 00:27:48,840
Who is the weakest link?

522
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:49,840
Vote.

523
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:52,600
Vote!

524
00:27:53,880 --> 00:27:54,880
You have to vote now.

525
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:56,120
I'm scared.

526
00:27:56,120 --> 00:27:58,120
Right now! Who will go first?

527
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:01,720
Sky.

528
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:02,480
Sky!

529
00:28:02,480 --> 00:28:04,400
Hey, Kree!

530
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:08,120
When you mispronounced "Chamomile" as "Chamomilee,"
I didn't even rub it in!

531
00:28:08,120 --> 00:28:09,840
I vote for Sky.

532
00:28:09,840 --> 00:28:10,600
Hmm.

533
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:13,320
Sky, you’ve been voted out.

534
00:28:13,320 --> 00:28:15,360
Please leave. They’ve already voted.

535
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:16,960
I’m sorry, Ms. Sky.

536
00:28:16,960 --> 00:28:20,960
You are not moving forward.
This airline is not the place for you.

537
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:23,040
Please leave.

538
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:28,280
How can you guys be this cruel to me?

539
00:28:28,280 --> 00:28:31,320
Where am I going to get money to spend?

540
00:28:31,320 --> 00:28:33,560
I'm still renting my house.

541
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:37,560
Every day, I'm even paying installments on my washing basin!

542
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:40,720
Not to mention the phone bill, water bill, and electricity.

543
00:28:40,720 --> 00:28:42,720
And I still have to support my man!

544
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:50,600
Don't even touch my hand, Kree! You jerk!

545
00:28:50,600 --> 00:28:54,520
Sky, I’m sorry. She forced me to vote, so I had to.

546
00:28:54,520 --> 00:28:56,680
I love this career so much.

547
00:28:56,680 --> 00:28:58,680
What kind of job am I going to do now?

548
00:29:04,960 --> 00:29:07,960
Well, well, well...

549
00:29:07,960 --> 00:29:11,960
Finally, I get to see Ms. Sky's tears.

550
00:29:12,560 --> 00:29:15,400
Ms. Petchgam Ploy, aren't you a bit too addicted to drama?

551
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:17,200
I wasn't finished.

552
00:29:17,200 --> 00:29:19,200
I was going to say that you are moving forward.

553
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:25,120
It’s because of your tears that I’ve softened up this much.

554
00:29:25,120 --> 00:29:26,120
Thank you!

555
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:29,600
Don't be confused. Look at me.

556
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:31,320
Because I want to push all of you.

557
00:29:31,320 --> 00:29:34,400
Push you to have the hunger to do a great job.

558
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:36,720
To make you the best First Class flight attendants.

559
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:37,560
Can you do it?

560
00:29:37,560 --> 00:29:38,480
Yes!

561
00:29:38,480 --> 00:29:39,400
I can't hear you. Can you do it?

562
00:29:39,400 --> 00:29:40,160
Yes!

563
00:29:40,160 --> 00:29:40,640
I still can't hear you!

564
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:41,640
YES!

565
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:47,320
Because you might not get another chance like this on the next flight.

566
00:29:47,320 --> 00:29:49,320
Do your best. See you later.

567
00:29:56,840 --> 00:29:58,520
You guys are all pieces of work!

568
00:29:58,520 --> 00:30:00,640
Hey, you got to stay, didn't you?

569
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:01,520
Don't touch me!

570
00:30:01,520 --> 00:30:02,520
Oh, come on.

571
00:30:02,520 --> 00:30:03,840
What if I really had to leave?

572
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:05,840
I haven't even finished paying off my helmet loan!

573
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:15,280
Just a little more...

574
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:16,720
Enough, enough, enough!

575
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:20,440
Are you okay now?

576
00:30:20,440 --> 00:30:21,440
Hey!

577
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:21,840
How is it? Good?

578
00:30:21,840 --> 00:30:22,920
The pain is gone.

579
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:26,920
Oh, it’s gone. But you know, it’s such a shame.

580
00:30:27,720 --> 00:30:29,720
I really want to go back to flying.

581
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:31,160
I miss the money.

582
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:33,560
Yeah, I want you back too.

583
00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:36,280
Flying without you...it feels like something is missing.

584
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:39,960
Being home is so lonely without you.

585
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:42,320
I just spend all my time on my phone.

586
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:46,320
Scrolling through the feed, and all I see are videos of kids.

587
00:30:50,680 --> 00:30:53,440
But they are pretty cute.

588
00:30:53,440 --> 00:30:56,160
I really wish I had one of my own.

589
00:30:56,160 --> 00:31:00,440
There you go again. You want to hire me as a surrogate?
If the money’s right, I’m down. No problem!

590
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:02,240
Are you serious?

591
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:04,680
Crazy! I'm joking.

592
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:08,080
At my age, and with this job, how could I have a kid?

593
00:31:08,080 --> 00:31:09,800
You should go freeze your eggs then.

594
00:31:09,800 --> 00:31:10,720
Freeze my eggs?

595
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:12,120
Yeah, I’ll help pay for it.

596
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:14,000
Ugh, I don’t even have a husband. Why bother freezing them?

597
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:15,360
I’m being serious, man.

598
00:31:15,360 --> 00:31:16,720
We already share a house.

599
00:31:17,160 --> 00:31:19,160
Sharing one more thing wouldn't hurt.

600
00:31:28,840 --> 00:31:35,840
Do you feel like we’re starting to act more and more like a married couple?

601
00:31:36,920 --> 00:31:38,560
Oops!

602
00:31:38,560 --> 00:31:42,560
Uh, actually, I’ve got a date with my ex tonight for a one-night stand.

603
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:47,360
By your leave, "Wifey."

604
00:31:47,360 --> 00:31:49,560
I've been deprived for too long!

605
00:31:49,560 --> 00:31:51,440
Thank you!

606
00:31:51,440 --> 00:31:55,440
Ugh, way to ruin a girl's dream.

607
00:31:55,760 --> 00:31:59,760
The end!

608
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:08,800
I think the two of us need to do a workshop together.

609
00:32:08,800 --> 00:32:11,320
About this "Old Money" and "New Money" thing.

610
00:32:11,320 --> 00:32:15,040
Because everywhere we walk, I’m so embarrassed.

611
00:32:15,040 --> 00:32:17,320
You are just so New Money.

612
00:32:17,320 --> 00:32:18,640
You can actually tell?

613
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:19,600
Well, yeah!

614
00:32:19,600 --> 00:32:23,280
Look at you. All the jewelry and accessories you wear...

615
00:32:23,280 --> 00:32:24,760
It’s exactly what New Money people wear.

616
00:32:24,760 --> 00:32:25,720
And what about you?

617
00:32:25,720 --> 00:32:28,160
Me? Everywhere I walk, I look distinguished.

618
00:32:28,160 --> 00:32:30,960
Everyone knows I’m Old Money.

619
00:32:30,960 --> 00:32:32,160
I believe you.

620
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:34,480
Because your face is definitely "Old."

621
00:32:34,480 --> 00:32:35,680
That's it! I'm not teaching you anymore.

622
00:32:35,680 --> 00:32:36,680
Hey, come on, teach me!

623
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:40,680
Okay, first thing first, the pronouns used to refer to yourself.

624
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:42,640
What do you think they use?

625
00:32:42,640 --> 00:32:45,720
Probably...

626
00:32:45,720 --> 00:32:46,760
I, myself...

627
00:32:46,760 --> 00:32:47,880
Are you a Thai traditional folk performer?

628
00:32:47,880 --> 00:32:48,800
Oh.

629
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:50,040
Listen to me.

630
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:53,280
I’ve been in high society a lot. To be Old Money,

631
00:32:53,920 --> 00:32:55,320
they use the word...

632
00:32:55,320 --> 00:32:56,080
Dance.

633
00:32:56,080 --> 00:32:56,840
What?

634
00:32:56,840 --> 00:32:57,800
Dance.

635
00:32:57,800 --> 00:32:59,120
Dance? Doesn't that mean dancing?

636
00:32:59,120 --> 00:33:02,040
See? You’re still stuck in your old, narrow boxes.

637
00:33:02,040 --> 00:33:04,320
Then what if Old Money people want to curse someone?

638
00:33:04,320 --> 00:33:05,200
What would they say?

639
00:33:05,200 --> 00:33:07,040
You're a cracked foot!

640
00:33:07,040 --> 00:33:07,640
Was that for me?

641
00:33:07,640 --> 00:33:09,920
No! Like, if Old Money people want to talk...

642
00:33:09,920 --> 00:33:11,280
like, "You idiot."

643
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:13,480
Actually, Old Money people don't really curse at each other.

644
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:14,120
I see.

645
00:33:14,120 --> 00:33:17,400
But they prioritize personality,

646
00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:20,040
walking, sitting, jewelry, and furniture.

647
00:33:20,040 --> 00:33:22,480
And the most important thing about being Old Money is...

648
00:33:22,480 --> 00:33:23,400
What?

649
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:25,160
...how you moan.

650
00:33:25,160 --> 00:33:27,240
Huh? There’s an "Old Money" way of moaning?

651
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:28,160
Yeah.

652
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:29,320
How does it go?

653
00:33:29,320 --> 00:33:32,680
Why don't you try moaning like New Money first?

654
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:33,560
Were you just slaughtered?

655
00:33:33,560 --> 00:33:35,240
No, it shouldn't be that loud.

656
00:33:35,240 --> 00:33:36,240
Listen.

657
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:39,800
Huh? That's it?

658
00:33:39,800 --> 00:33:41,960
Yeah, that's how they moan.

659
00:33:43,520 --> 00:33:45,320
Whoa, just like that!

660
00:33:45,320 --> 00:33:46,680
Just like that and you're Old Money?

661
00:33:46,680 --> 00:33:47,680
Yep.

662
00:33:47,880 --> 00:33:49,040
All-New.

663
00:33:49,040 --> 00:33:50,000
Come on, let’s help carry this.

664
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:51,000
Okay.

665
00:33:51,680 --> 00:33:53,680
Oh, I don't think the two of us will make it.
I’ll do it. Let's go.

666
00:33:57,760 --> 00:33:59,960
Chaba, are you alright?

667
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:02,160
Damn, I almost broke the counter.

668
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:03,520
Just wait until I meet the real you.

669
00:34:03,520 --> 00:34:05,280
All-New, you just carry it yourself. Go!

670
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:06,320
Go!

671
00:34:06,320 --> 00:34:07,760
This "wax" thing has crossed the line way too many times.

672
00:34:07,760 --> 00:34:09,600
Oh! Look, now she's jumping.

673
00:34:09,600 --> 00:34:10,600
You, New Money...wait until I see you.

674
00:34:13,480 --> 00:34:15,000
The sun is just so hot...

675
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:17,600
I'm not a robot that can stand in the sun all day.

676
00:34:17,600 --> 00:34:19,640
I want to buy a robot of my own,

677
00:34:19,640 --> 00:34:23,640
To use in the kitchen, to farm, and to dig up some yams.

678
00:34:23,760 --> 00:34:25,000
Cute!

679
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:27,920
Wait, you watch soccer too?

680
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:28,600
Who do you support?

681
00:34:28,600 --> 00:34:30,280
I’m a Gooner, an Arsenal disciple.

682
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:31,840
Since the Arsène Van-ger...

683
00:34:31,840 --> 00:34:34,840
Arsène Wen-Wenger...

684
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:36,240
Arsène Wenger era...

685
00:34:36,240 --> 00:34:37,680
Since the time Arsène Wenger...Okay! Let’s just get to the point!

686
00:34:37,680 --> 00:34:39,840
Just having to search for the "aesthetic"...

687
00:34:39,840 --> 00:34:40,960
Or what translates to "Aesthetics" in Thai...

688
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:43,200
of Ms. Crown,

689
00:34:43,200 --> 00:34:46,960
I'm so discouraged I’m about to quit this job, Sky!

690
00:34:46,960 --> 00:34:48,280
I mean...Chaba!

691
00:34:49,840 --> 00:34:51,040
Again! Sorry, sorry!

692
00:34:51,560 --> 00:34:52,440
Are you scared of me?

693
00:34:52,440 --> 00:34:53,840
I’m not scared, but the people next to us are staring.

694
00:34:53,840 --> 00:34:55,560
I want to see myself in a mirror.

695
00:34:55,560 --> 00:34:57,160
Don’t look at it.

696
00:34:57,160 --> 00:34:57,880
Oh, shit!

697
00:34:57,880 --> 00:35:01,240
Whoa, that’s scary!

698
00:35:01,240 --> 00:35:02,480
What do I do now?

699
00:35:05,360 --> 00:35:06,320
Freeze my eggs? Why bother?

700
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:10,240
I don't even have a husband.

701
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,240
What's next?

702
00:35:13,640 --> 00:35:14,520
This way, Ms. Daryl.

703
00:35:14,520 --> 00:35:16,160
This is going to be so much fun!

704
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:17,240
Chaba!

705
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:19,080
Why on earth is your passenger wearing a raincoat?

706
00:35:19,080 --> 00:35:19,960
It's fashion!

707
00:35:19,960 --> 00:35:20,960
Oh, fashion. Got it.

708
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:27,000
Um, is this really a First Class airline?

709
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:32,120
Sorry, sorry! Let’s go again!

710
00:35:36,880 --> 00:35:37,800
I bet they’re having a one-night stand right now.

711
00:35:37,800 --> 00:35:40,880
If I don’t get any good sleep,
don’t you dare dream of going to heaven!

712
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:42,280
I'll show you!

713
00:35:42,280 --> 00:35:43,720
Your stuff is a total mess.

714
00:35:43,720 --> 00:35:44,400
Clean it up, will you?

715
00:35:44,400 --> 00:35:47,400
Chai, you jerk! You were doing it so loudly,
how was I supposed to sleep?

716
00:35:48,720 --> 00:35:49,600
Oh my god!

717
00:35:49,600 --> 00:35:51,960
I am the "President of this Village," okay?

718
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:52,720
You never clean the house!

719
00:35:52,720 --> 00:35:54,160
This place is messy, dirty, and disgusting!

720
00:35:54,160 --> 00:35:57,200
What about you?
You bring both men and women over to do it at this house!

721
00:35:57,200 --> 00:35:59,320
If you’re so annoyed by me, then just move out!

722
00:35:59,320 --> 00:36:01,000
I’m not leaving!

723
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:01,640
You have to leave!

724
00:36:01,640 --> 00:36:02,400
No, YOU leave!

725
00:36:02,400 --> 00:36:02,720
- You leave!
- You leave!

726
00:36:03,080 --> 00:36:04,040
- You leave!
- You leave!
